As Chris wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/19/2004 at 18:53:20 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>I am a tower crane engineer Operating a new type of crane with a
>German computer. The only glitz in this computer is the wind sensor
>registers in feet per second instead of MPH. I would like to know
>formular for converting feet per second to MPH.
>
>[Difficulty]
>I am not sure of the conversion.
>
>[Thoughts]
>

Thanks for writing to Ask Dr. Math!

Since 1 foot = 1/5280 miles, and 1 second = 1/3600 hours, you have

   1 foot/sec = (1/5280)/(1/3600) miles/hour,
              = 3600/5280 miles/hour,
              = 15/22 miles/hour.

Feel free to reply if I can help further with this question.


